ed from <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>hard</i> ‘brave, hardy, strong’. In the later Middle Ages this was a more common name than   Gerald  , with which it was sometimes confused. Nowadays it is less common, surviving mainly among Roman Catholics, in honour of the many saints of this name."],"variants":[{"name":"Gerrard","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Gerard  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]},{"name":"Jerrard","meanings":["Rare variant spelling of   Gerard  , probably influenced by the form of the modern surname, if not a transferred use."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gerard d'Enghien was born about 1290, in France, his father, Chevalier Sohier d'Enghien, was 27 and his mother, Beatrix de Raineval, was 2. He married Marie de Rumigny in Fagnolle, Namur, Belgium. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1368, in Havré, Hainaut, Belgium, at the age of 79, and was buried in Mons, Hainaut, Belgium."},"et":{"Abt 1290–1368":"umbes 1290–1368","1290–1368":"1290–1368","1303–1356":"1303–1356","1298–1358":"1298–1358","1305–1364":"1305–1364","–1385":"–1385","1265–1327":"1265–1327","1290–1339":"1290–1339","October 1327":"oktoober 1327","1385":"1385","05 DEC 1364":"5. detsember 1364","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1305":"1305","1358":"1358","1303":"1303","BEF 13 FEB 1358":"enne 13. veebruari 1358","1368":"1368","1356":"1356","1265":"1265","1364":"1364","1298":"1298","25 March 1339":"25. märts 1339","about 1310":"umbes 1310","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","1339":"1339","Mons, Hainaut, Belgium":"Mons, Hainaut, Belgia","Havré, 959, Hainaut, Belgique":"Havré, Hainaut, Belgia","France":"Prantsusmaa","Fagnolle, Namur, Belgique":"Fagnolle, Namur, Belgia"},"fi":{"Abt 1290–1368":"noin 1290–1368","1290–1368":"1290–1368","1303–1356":"1303–1356","1298–1358":"1298–1358","1305–1364":"1305–1364","–1385":"–1385","1265–1327":"1265–1327","1290–1339":"1290–1339","October 1327":"lokakuu 1327","1385":"1385","05 DEC 1364":"5. joulukuuta 1364","1290":"1